WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.044
Good morning, Jacob. It's Saturday, April eleventh, twenty twenty-six, in

00:00:04.044 --> 00:00:08.087
Jefferson City. And Artemis Two is home. The crew climbed

00:00:08.087 --> 00:00:12.131
out of the capsule in the Pacific last night —

00:00:12.131 --> 00:00:16.174
eight oh seven P-M Eastern, about forty to fifty miles

00:00:16.174 --> 00:00:20.218
off San Diego. Wiseman, Glover, Koch, and Hansen, all healthy,

00:00:20.218 --> 00:00:24.262
all recovered cleanly by the U-S-S John P. Murtha. Nine-day

00:00:24.262 --> 00:00:28.305
mission. Distance record broken on the way out. First crewed

00:00:28.305 --> 00:00:32.349
lunar mission since Apollo Seventeen in December of nineteen seventy-two.

00:00:32.349 --> 00:00:36.392
Fifty-three and a half years. The thing that was supposed

00:00:36.392 --> 00:00:40.436
to happen actually happened, and it's worth letting that register

00:00:40.436 --> 00:00:44.480
for half a second before the rest of the world

00:00:44.480 --> 00:00:48.523
piles back in. It's eighty-three degrees and sunny in Jefferson

00:00:48.523 --> 00:00:52.567
City today. Mostly sunny, light southeast wind, shifting southwest. Low

00:00:52.567 --> 00:00:56.610
around forty-six tonight. This is genuinely the best day of

00:00:56.610 --> 00:01:00.654
the year so far. If you spend it indoors, you'll

00:01:00.654 --> 00:01:04.698
regret it. Now, the calendar. The Google Calendar A-P-I is

00:01:04.698 --> 00:01:08.741
still returning ancient events — same failure as yesterday. So

00:01:08.741 --> 00:01:12.785
I'm treating today as an open Saturday. By context: the

00:01:12.785 --> 00:01:16.828
Pinwheels of Possibilities resource fair is on the South Capitol

00:01:16.828 --> 00:01:20.872
Lawn from ten A-M to noon — Child Abuse Prevention

00:01:20.872 --> 00:01:24.915
Month event, three blocks from home. And the U-S-Iran talks

00:01:24.915 --> 00:01:28.959
open in Islamabad all day today. You don't have a

00:01:28.959 --> 00:01:33.003
role in this, but it's what the news cycle will

00:01:33.003 --> 00:01:37.046
orbit. Speaking of Islamabad. Vance is on the ground with

00:01:37.046 --> 00:01:41.090
Steve Witkoff and Jared Kushner. The Iranian delegation is already

00:01:41.090 --> 00:01:45.133
there — Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi and parliament speaker Mohammad

00:01:45.133 --> 00:01:49.177
Bagher Ghalibaf. This is the first formal session of the

00:01:49.177 --> 00:01:53.221
highest-level U-S-Iran talks since the nineteen seventy-nine Islamic Revolution, which

00:01:53.221 --> 00:01:57.264
is a sentence that should cause a brief moment of

00:01:57.264 --> 00:02:01.308
vertigo if you stop to take it in. Three things

00:02:01.308 --> 00:02:05.351
to actually watch today: the joint readout — if nothing

00:02:05.351 --> 00:02:09.395
by tomorrow morning, the first session didn't go well. The

00:02:09.395 --> 00:02:13.439
Lebanon language — whether Lebanon is mentioned at all in

00:02:13.439 --> 00:02:17.482
any official statement. And the Hormuz tolls — if they

00:02:17.482 --> 00:02:21.526
get addressed, it's real diplomacy. If they don't, it's theater.

00:02:21.526 --> 00:02:25.569
The Atlantic's Will Gottsegen has the counter-consensus take worth absorbing:

00:02:25.569 --> 00:02:29.613
Iran walks into Islamabad with structural leverage. They control the

00:02:29.613 --> 00:02:33.657
Strait of Hormuz. Hezbollah is a free escalation option. The

00:02:33.657 --> 00:02:37.700
U-S political clock is running faster than theirs. Manifold agrees

00:02:37.700 --> 00:02:41.744
— the market for a second Iran ceasefire in twenty

00:02:41.744 --> 00:02:45.787
twenty-six jumped from forty-one percent to seventy-five percent overnight. Traders

00:02:45.787 --> 00:02:49.831
are saying this one won't hold. Now, the Mythos cascade.

00:02:49.831 --> 00:02:53.875
Chapter two. Three things in the last thirty-six hours paint

00:02:53.875 --> 00:02:57.918
a picture of Anthropic under real pressure. One: an OpenAI

00:02:57.918 --> 00:03:01.962
researcher's Reddit post that his Anthropic roommate, quote, lost his

00:03:01.962 --> 00:03:06.005
mind over Mythos. Two: Stella Laurenzo, A-M-D's Director of A-I,

00:03:06.005 --> 00:03:10.049
filed a detailed GitHub issue on April second documenting Claude

00:03:10.049 --> 00:03:14.093
Code degradation across nearly seven thousand sessions. She found thinking

00:03:14.093 --> 00:03:18.136
depth dropped roughly sixty-seven percent after Anthropic deployed thinking content

00:03:18.136 --> 00:03:22.180
redaction in early March. Her team has already switched to

00:03:22.180 --> 00:03:26.223
another provider. Three: Anthropic is now banning users under eighteen

00:03:26.223 --> 00:03:30.267
via Yoti third-party age verification, with manual review of chat

00:03:30.267 --> 00:03:34.311
histories. Read these together and the picture is: strained internal

00:03:34.311 --> 00:03:38.354
culture, public quality critique from a peer company's A-I director,

00:03:38.354 --> 00:03:42.398
and defensive policy tightening. None of this should change your

00:03:42.398 --> 00:03:46.441
decision to apply for the Sales role — if anything,

00:03:46.441 --> 00:03:50.485
a company in this posture needs more, not fewer, competent

00:03:50.485 --> 00:03:54.529
operators with government-procurement chops. Project Glasswing is now officially on

00:03:54.529 --> 00:03:58.572
anthropic dot com. The partner list is broader than the

00:03:58.572 --> 00:04:02.616
early leaks suggested: A-W-S, Apple, Broadcom, Cisco, CrowdStrike, Google, JPMorgan

00:04:02.616 --> 00:04:06.659
Chase, the Linux Foundation, Microsoft, NVIDIA, and Palo Alto Networks.

00:04:06.659 --> 00:04:10.703
That's the entire American cyber-industrial establishment in one coalition. Anthropic

00:04:10.703 --> 00:04:14.746
is committing one hundred million dollars in Mythos Preview credits

00:04:14.746 --> 00:04:18.790
plus four million in open-source security donations. A ninety-day public

00:04:18.790 --> 00:04:22.834
report is promised for early July. The absent name is

00:04:22.834 --> 00:04:26.877
the one you'd expect most: Meta. And the hard data

00:04:26.877 --> 00:04:30.921
on the war premium is finally in. March C-P-I came

00:04:30.921 --> 00:04:34.964
in at three point three percent, up from two point

00:04:34.964 --> 00:04:39.008
four in February. Energy costs plus ten point nine percent.

00:04:39.008 --> 00:04:43.052
Gasoline plus twenty-one point two percent — the biggest monthly

00:04:43.052 --> 00:04:47.095
jump on record. Core inflation was only plus point two,

00:04:47.095 --> 00:04:51.139
so this is entirely the Hormuz-Brent shock showing up in

00:04:51.139 --> 00:04:55.182
the headline number. It makes the Fed's second-half rate-cut thesis

00:04:55.182 --> 00:04:59.226
materially harder. Quick hits. The D-C Circuit declined to block

00:04:59.226 --> 00:05:03.270
the Pentagon's supply-chain-risk label on Anthropic — the same label

00:05:03.270 --> 00:05:07.313
creating friction for your Claude pilot at Budget and Planning.

00:05:07.313 --> 00:05:11.357
France launched a government Linux desktop plan — nineteen thousand

00:05:11.357 --> 00:05:15.400
upvotes on r slash technology, digital sovereignty framing. Tesla is

00:05:15.400 --> 00:05:19.444
in its eighth consecutive week of losses, JPMorgan warns sixty

00:05:19.444 --> 00:05:23.488
percent downside. Sam Altman's home was targeted with a Molotov

00:05:23.488 --> 00:05:27.531
cocktail — no injuries, suspect arrested, but the A-I backlash

00:05:27.531 --> 00:05:31.575
narrative now has a physical-violence dimension. Apple Q one numbers

00:05:31.575 --> 00:05:35.618
are quietly great: Mac shipments plus nine percent, and Apple

00:05:35.618 --> 00:05:39.662
led global smartphone shipments for the first time in Q

00:05:39.662 --> 00:05:43.706
one with twenty-one percent share. Alright. Here's the thing. Yesterday,

00:05:43.706 --> 00:05:47.749
Katelyn green-lit the Anthropic application. Explicitly. The Apple Note titled

00:05:47.749 --> 00:05:51.793
Why Anthropic, asterisk, on your phone was last touched Thursday

00:05:51.793 --> 00:05:55.836
morning with an asterisk you added yourself. Katelyn said yes.

00:05:55.836 --> 00:05:59.880
The weather is perfect. You know what today is for.

00:05:59.880 --> 00:06:03.924
The activation energy work is done. Today is a first

00:06:03.924 --> 00:06:07.967
draft, not a finished masterpiece. Write it by noon, and

00:06:07.967 --> 00:06:12.011
you can spend the rest of the day outside without

00:06:12.011 --> 00:06:16.054
a single voice in your head telling you you should

00:06:16.054 --> 00:06:20.098
be doing something else. Artemis Two is home. The Capitol

00:06:20.098 --> 00:06:24.142
dome is still blue for Child Abuse Prevention Month. Islamabad

00:06:24.142 --> 00:06:28.185
is talking. And you have a cover letter to finish.

00:06:28.185 --> 00:06:31.420
That's your briefing. Go outside at some point.
